The wait is now over as Nigerian versatile artiste and songwriter, who is famous as The Kclaut, has released his much anticipated single, ‘Fan Love’. The song has been the talk of the town for weeks with fans urging the budding singer to make true his claim of giving them another melodious tune. As soon as the song was dropped, Fan Love recorded multiple downloads and streamed across multiple platforms. Produced by popular beat maker, Smoothkiss, The Kclaut, described the song as a good time song for every class of people. He added that he expected the ” catchy tune to rock clubs and top billboard charts and airwaves across the globe. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…With ‘Fan Love’.  With ‘Fan Love’ Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…With ‘Fan Love’. With ‘Fan Love’ ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
